
An overview of *possible* assignment of options letters, including those
used by Make.  

-a
-b
-B    M   Re-make all
-c
-d
-e        Expression
-f  S M   File
-g
-h  S M   Help
-i    M   Ignore all errors in commands
-I    M   Include path
-j  S M   Parallel
-k  S M   Keep going
-l        
-L    M   special handling of symlinks
-m        Mode (e.g., random order, etc.)
-n    M   Dry run (just print commands)
-o    M   Mark file as old
-p    M   Print database (rule set)
-q    M   Question mode / Query mode
-r        
-s  S M   Silent
-S    M   No keep going
-t    M   Touch instead of building
-u
-v  S M   Verbose
-V  S     Version
-w
-W    M   What-if mode (if FILE just had been modified)
-x
-y
-z


S:  implemented in Stu
M:  compatible with Make
